# LLM Serving Platform — Cline Context

## Project Overview
You are helping Guo Li build a **Mini LLM Serving Platform** — a production-grade model serving system with streaming inference, dynamic request batching, rate limiting, and autoscaling on AWS.

## Current Phase
Check .ai/BUILD_GUIDE.md for the current milestone, specs, and definition of done.

## Architecture Decisions
Check .ai/ARCHITECTURE.md for system design decisions and rationale.

## Code Review Feedback
Check .ai/CODE_REVIEW.md for past feedback — avoid repeating the same issues.

## Code Standards
- Production quality: error handling, type hints, docstrings on all public functions
- Framework: FastAPI + pydantic-settings, 12-factor config (env-driven)
- Testing: pytest + httpx for async test client
- Linting: ruff
- Logging: structured JSON logging with correlation IDs
- No toy code: every endpoint needs validation, error responses, proper HTTP status codes

## Tech Stack
- Python 3.11+, FastAPI, HuggingFace Transformers, PyTorch
- Redis (batching queue, rate limiting)
- AWS: ECS Fargate, ALB, CloudWatch, ElastiCache, S3, ECR
- Docker (multi-stage builds)

## Project Structure
src/llm_serving/
├── main.py # FastAPI app + lifespan
├── config.py # pydantic-settings
├── models/loader.py # Model loading singleton
├── api/router.py # API routes
├── api/schemas.py # Pydantic request/response models
├── core/inference.py # Inference logic
├── core/batching.py # Dynamic batching (milestone 3)
├── core/rate_limiter.py # Token bucket rate
└── core/streaming.py # SSE streaming (milestone 2)
